    "We categorize the RD exam questions into different subgroups, within which the LLMs' inaccurate responses are assessed.",
    "To achieve this, we analyze the errors obtained in terms of proficiency levels and four nutrition domains (i.e., topics).",
    "Proficiency Levels: The approaches are evaluated based on the questions' proficiency levels, provided by the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics, eatrightPREP for the RDN Exam 42.",
    "The exam consists of 149 Easy, 352 Moderate, 392 Difficult, and 149 Expert levels questions.",
    "Figure 2a shows the average errors for each approach."
  ],
